Data exploration and first-round prepocessing¶

================================================

  1. Convert waveforms to arrays and store H5 using generator function (not whole script)

  2. Load catalog, create columns

    • evID
    • timestamp

    • filename

      • for filename, need to make separate catalog with event IDs generated from filename, then merge that catalog with the original

      and save out CSV with labeled column names

  3. Apply generate_features to waveforms (may have to adapt for H5 arrays)

     * generate some timelines, look for outliers
 * Spectral centroid, RSAM, P2P
  1. Plot features, maps

wf_list = glob.glob(pathWF + '*')

filenames = [path.split('/')[-1] for path in wf_list]

ev_ID = [int(path.split('/')[-1].split('.')[-1]) for path in wf_list]

cat_paths = pd.DataFrame({"ev_ID":ev_ID,
                          "filename":filenames})

Plot Features over time¶

In [22]:
features = ['log10RSAM','SpecCentr','log10P2P','log10Var','Kurt','DomFreq','magnitude','depth_km']

for feat in features:
    print(feat)
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))
    
    
    
    plt.title(feat,fontsize=24)
    plt.xlabel('Date',fontsize=16)
    plt.scatter(x=cat_feat['timestamp'],
                y=cat_feat[feat],
                s=4,
                c='k',
                alpha=.6)  
    
    plt.savefig(f'../reports/figures/preprocess_{feat}.png')
